      • getFullMeasureCount

        public int getFullMeasureCount()
        Returns the number of full measures in this score.

        Pickup measures are not counted, that is, the number of measures is the same as the largest measure number in the score.

        Returns:
        the number of full measures in this score

      • getMeasureCount

        public int getMeasureCount()
        Returns the number of measures in this score.

        Pickup measures are included in the counte, that is, the number of measures is the same as the largest measure number in the score plus a possible pickup measure.

        Returns:
        the number of full measures in this score

      • getAt

        public Pattern getAt​(PatternPosition patternPosition)
              throws java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Returns the pattern specified by the given pattern position in this score.

        The returned pattern contains a voice for each staff that the pattern position refers to. If the pattern position refers to a staff that has multiple voices and any of the notes referred to by the pattern overlap, then separate pattern voices are created for each of the voices within the staff.

        The pattern contains only those notes that are included in the pattern specified by the position, the intermediate notes are replaced by padding rests.

        Parameters:
        patternPosition - the position for which the pattern is returned
        Returns:
        the pattern specified by the given pattern position in this score
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if the pattern position refers to a note outside the score

      • partwiseIterator

        public PositionalIterator partwiseIterator()
        Returns an iterator that iterates the durational notation objects in partwise order.

        Starts by iterating through the part with the smallest number. Iterates through parts starting from smallest measure number. Iterates through measure voice by voice.

        Returns:
        an iterator that iterates the durational notation objects in partwise order
